# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OSes or Python versions,
#   keeping Pipfile.lock might cause conflicts.
# /Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#   checked in to version control. However, in some cases it is ignored.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
# /pdm.lock

